  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel delivery from tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kumara Rajapaksa, President of the Fuel Station Owners Association, said today (20) that fuel distribution will be done from tomorrow (21) through the filling stations of the Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation nationwide based on the last digit of the vehicle number plate.",
        "He mentioned that vehicles with 3, 4 and 5 final digits will be given fuel today.",
        "The Ministry of Energy has announced that fuel will be supplied to the final digits 0,1,2 on Tuesday and Saturday, 3,4,5 on Thursday and Sunday and 6,7,8,9 on Monday, Wednesday and Friday.",
        "Fuel will be provided on the basis of Rs.1500 for motorcycles, Rs.2000 for autos and Rs.7000 for cars and vans.",
        "Meanwhile, the Ministry has decided to implement the fuel distribution as per the National Fuel Permit as a pilot project for 4 days from 21st at the selected fuel filling stations in Colombo district.",
        "It is noteworthy that the Minister of Energy Kanjana Wijesekara has said that the National Fuel Permit System will be implemented from the 25th onwards."
      ],
